args: Ohhh ho ho ho ho!\nOhhhhh ho ho ho ho ho!
Good people of the Halidom, thank you all\nfor attending this year's Valentine's party,\nhosted by yours truly, Catherine.
We've done our utmost to make it a truly\nspectacular event. Now, go forth and revel!
Wow, you really went all-out, Cat!\nThis is a shindig for the history books!
Naturally. Perfection demands I do nothing\nless, regardless of the occasion.
Among other party favors, I have made\ncertain that every guest has received their\ncomplimentary thank-you gift.
All but one, that is... *sigh*\nWhere the devil is he hiding?
Gross. There're way too many people here.\nThis spectacle's offending all my senses.\nWorst of all...
Melsaaa! Here you go! I baked\nrose-shaped cookies, just for you!
For me?! Awww, Sarisse! I love them!
Felicia... Are you certain it's wise for\nme to attend a party?
An invitation for me is an invitation for the\nboth of us. It wouldn't be the same without\nyou anyway. Now, let's head in, Phantom!
(I want to give this to her. I really do.\nThat's the only reason I came at all, but...)
(I'm an introvert lost in a sea of extroverts\nhere. I stick out like a sore thumb.)
Oof... It's, uh, Addis, right?\nUm... Thanks.
No big. Your sweet treat here almost ate\ndirt, though. Managed to catch it before it\nhit the floor.
Ha ha. Tuck that away someplace safe.\nIt's a gift for someone, yeah?
Something like that. That's kind of\nthe whole reason I'm here, but...
But you're not much of a party guy,\nso you decided to cut and run?
Grk! Hey, get off my back.\nSome of us just suck at small talk.\nBesides, not like she'd even notice if I le—
HRFH! Catherine?!\nWhat the heck was THAT for?!
My apologies. A reflexive reaction after I\nfinally spotted you and came to say hello,\nthen caught you slinking off like a weasel.
Regrettably, yes. I figured you would wait\nout the holiday hunkered down alone\nsomewhere. That's why I invited you.
If... If you're in such a rush to leave,\nthen go. I certainly won't stop you.
Now, if you'll excuse me,\nI have a party to host.
Ouch... Guess you ended up eating dirt\nafter all, if only in a metaphorical sense.
You think I don't know it's my own fault?
Catherine and I used to be at each other's\nthroats all the time, but lately we've been\ngetting along better...
So I wanted to...\nY'know, say thanks, I guess.
If that was you two ＂getting along＂ back\nthere, you've got a funny way of doing it.\nThat's tough, bud.
Whatever. I'm not worried...\nLike I said, we fight all the time.
It's not like forcing myself to give her\nsomething for Valentine's is gonna change\nthat.
If you say so. You know best. But...you\nstill want to tell her how you feel, right?
Even if it's nothing life-changing,\nsometimes you've just gotta speak\nfrom the heart or forever hold your peace.
You can tell a lot about a guy from how he\nacts when the gauntlet's thrown down.\nCould be this is one of those moments.
You know what? I wanna be somebody\nwho bucks up when the going gets rough.
Sounds like that's your cue, then. The\nrest just comes down to having the guts.
(I didn't set out to pick a fight. I rehearsed\nmy line and everything. I wanted to tell\nhim I'm happy we've gotten closer.)
(I even went to the trouble of preparing\na Valentine's present for him.)
But when have I ever been transparent\nabout my feelings? Why start now?\nI'll just get rid of—
What is it? Come to lodge a\ncomplaint about my party?
What?! No! Why do you always have to\npick a fight as soon as I open my mouth?
And you wonder why I always throw the\nsnark right back at you!
Excuse me?! All YOU ever do is whine and\ncomplain! That's why I always have to set\nyou straight!
Oh, so it's all MY fault?\nAugh, you're infuriating!
You took the words right out of my mouth!\nI've heard quite enough. I'm VERY busy, so\nif you'll excuse me!
(That's not... That wasn't what I wanted\nto say to her. I... I—)
What? You want the last word that badly?
You're damn right I do.\nI'm throwing down the gauntlet.
Er... Are you challenging me to a duel?
Yup. This is between you and me. I'll\nface you head-on from here on out. So...
Eugene, did you...get this? For me?
You got a problem with that? You think a\nguy like me isn't grateful for all you do for\nme? You think I don't want you know it?!
Hmph. Well, it seems I lose this round.
Wait, you got me something too?
Shocking, I know. Honestly, I'd given up\non handing it over to you until just now.
You beat me to the punch, AND you're the\nonly reason I was able to give you mine.\nConsider today a win for Eugene.
Catherine, I... Wow. I was just about to\ncall it quits on giving you my present, too.
Is that so? And here I thought you were\nbeginning to show a bit of spine. Once\na coward, always a coward, I suppose.
Oh, please. Like you didn't chicken out too.\nReeeal brave, Little Miss Perfect.
Hey, all that matters is that I delivered it\nin the end. My perfect record stands.\n...Thanks to you.
And, uh... I used to think people who\nmade a big fuss over Valentine's were\nall idiots, but...
This year was...actually kinda fun.\n...Thanks to you.
